REASONING: The CIA World Factbook shows Singapore ranks #1 in Real GDP per capita (PPP) at $132,600 for 2024, ahead of Luxembourg ($128,200) and other countries
However, the Wikipedia data on nominal GDP per capita shows Monaco at $256,581, Liechtenstein at $207,973, and Luxembourg at $140,941 (2025 estimates) ranking higher than other countries
The Singapore Ministry of Industry and Trade website claims Singapore ranks among the world's top five in GDP per capita, not first
There are different measures of GDP per capita - nominal GDP per capita and real GDP per capita (PPP adjusted) - which produce different rankings
Based on PPP-adjusted real GDP per capita from CIA World Factbook, Singapore does rank #1, but based on nominal GDP per capita from other sources, several small countries/territories rank higher
